It is an embarrassing condition that affects thousands if not millions of people smelly feet syndrome. A condition caused by increased sweating of the feet with no space for evaporation, creating a conducive environment for bacteria and dead skin to grow, leading to a bad odor. This is how you can ensure your feet don’t stink: 1. Cut your nails short. 2. Wipe between your toes after washing them. 3. Use cotton socks instead of synthetic socks. 4. Disinfect your foot wear 5. Walk barefoot while in the house. 6. Have several pairs of shoes. 